Round 1 
[Patient] What foods should I eat to help with my heart failure? 
[Educator] Focus on fruits, veggies, whole grains, and lean protein like fish or chicken.

Round 2 
[Patient] Can I still eat my favorite fried foods? 
[Educator] Limit fried foods to special occasions, try baking or grilling instead.

Round 3 
[Patient] How much salt should I have in my diet? 
[Educator] Try to limit salt intake to less than 2,300 mg per day.

Round 4 
[Patient] Are there any specific foods I should avoid? 
[Educator] Avoid processed foods, high-sodium snacks, and sugary drinks.

Round 5 
[Patient] What about alcohol, is that okay? 
[Educator] Limit alcohol intake to moderate levels, talk to your doctor for specifics.

Round 6 
[Patient] Can I still have dessert sometimes? 
[Educator] Opt for healthier dessert options like fruit or yogurt instead of high-sugar treats.

Round 7 
[Patient] How important is it to stay hydrated? 
[Educator] Stay hydrated by drinking plenty of water, aim for at least 8 cups a day.

Round 8 
[Patient] Should I be eating more fiber in my diet? 
[Educator] Yes, include high-fiber foods like whole grains, beans, and nuts in your diet.

Round 9 
[Patient] Are there any specific types of fats I should avoid? 
[Educator] Limit saturated fats found in red meat, cheese, and fried foods.

Round 10 
[Patient] What about portion sizes, how much should I be eating? 
[Educator] Pay attention to portion sizes, use smaller plates and listen to your body's hunger cues.

Round 11 
[Patient] Can I still have coffee or tea? 
[Educator] Enjoy coffee and tea in moderation, but watch out for added sugars and cream.

Round 12 
[Patient] Are there any specific heart-healthy foods I should be eating more of? 
[Educator] Include foods rich in omega-3 fatty acids like salmon, walnuts, and flaxseeds.

Round 13 
[Patient] What about fast food, is that completely off limits? 
[Educator] Limit fast food as much as possible, opt for healthier options when dining out.

Round 14 
[Patient] How can I make sure I'm getting enough nutrients in my diet? 
[Educator] Eat a variety of colorful fruits and veggies to ensure you're getting a range of nutrients.

